-- John Terry Faces Backlash Over Challenge to Capello: Soccer Roundup
-- Peter-Joseph Hegarty
-- 2010-06-21T10:32:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-21/john-terry-faces-backlash-over-challenge-to-capello-soccer-roundup.html

          
          
             The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  
 Terry Backlash?  
 England’s  John Terry  faces an “angry backlash” from his
teammates after attempting to challenge coach  Fabio Capello ’s
authority,  the Independent  reported.  
 Terry’s comments at a news conference, before the squad’s
meeting with Capello last night, caused “derision and
disbelief” among the players, the newspaper said.  
 Terry told reporters he was ready to “upset” the coach if
necessary if it helped England win the World Cup, following two
draws.  
 The coach made some “nominal” concessions to appease the
squad but appeared to have nullified “player power,” the
Guardian reported.  
 At a televised news conference today, England’s  Frank Lampard  said there are no factions in the camp and the players
fully support Capello.  
 Gerrard Price Tag  
 Real Madrid wants Liverpool to drop its 30 million-pound
($44 million) valuation of  Steven Gerrard  as it tries to
complete the purchase of the England midfielder, the  Daily Mail 
reported.  
 Zamora for Blues?  
 Birmingham is reviving its interest in Fulham striker  Bobby Zamora , the  Daily Mail  reported.  
 The Blues are hoping to exploit uncertainty over the
position of Fulham coach  Roy Hodgson , who’s been linked with a
move to Liverpool.  
 Blackburn Target  
 Blackburn may move for Croatia striker Nikica Jelavic, the
 Daily Mirror  reported. Coach  Sam Allardyce ’s “spies” have been
assessing the Rapid Vienna player, it added.  
